Matthew S. Kissner
Independent Member
USRP Board of Directors











Download (.PDF)
                





In addition to his role with U.S. Retirement Partners, Matthew S. Kissner is chair- man-designate of Wiley, a leading publishing company. He is also a Board Member of Regional Plan Association where he is Treasurer and a member of the Executive Committee.
Mr. Kissner has extensive operating experience in Business and Financial Services. His career includes Pitney Bowes, Banker’s Trust Company, Morgan Stanley and Citibank. Mr. Kissner was Executive Vice President of Pitney Bowes Inc. and Group President of Global Enterprise Solutions, reporting to the Chairman & Chief Executive Officer. From January 2006 to December 2007, he was Chairman of American Radiology Services, which was successfully sold to a strategic buyer.
Mr. Kissner’s experience includes consumer, small business and large enterprise/ government markets. He has extensive operations experience, including responsibility for a 15,000 person global outsourcing business, sales, service and collections call centers, consumer and business credit, and retail banking branch sys- tems. In his 33 year career, he has successfully led operations through rapid growth as well as consolidations, utilizing a strong process management and six sigma orientation. Mr. Kissner has managed multi-channel distribution, geographically dispersed operations, and technology-based scalable operations. He has a track record of achieving double digit revenue and profit growth through developing new business models, creating a strong customer focus, and building talent.
Mr. Kissner received his Bachelor of Science and MBA degrees with honors from New York University.




























