Our Team










 Matthew Kissner 
Matthew S. Kissner is President and Chief Executive Officer of The Kissner Group LLC and an Operating Partner of Advent International, one of the world’s leading private equity firms.  He is focused on investment opportunities involving high potential mid-size companies where there is a significant growth opportunity through building strong management teams along with scalable business processes and technology.Mr. Kissner is primarily focused on services where his experiences in banking, financial and credit services, customer care and managed services, controls, compliance, confidentiality and low defect rates are paramount, and where rapid product innovation and superior talent have proven to be sources of competitive advantage.His twenty-six year career includes multiple industries and roles with Pitney Bowes, Banker’s Trust Company, Morgan Stanley and Citibank.  Most recently, Mr. Kissner was Executive Vice President of Pitney Bowes Inc. and Group President of Global Enterprise Solutions, reporting to the Chairman & Chief Executive Officer.  This group focused on expanding Pitney Bowes’ competitive position with large commercial enterprises and government, accounting for $1.4 billion in annual revenues.  In 2004, Global Enterprise Solutions experienced 15% revenue growth and 36% EBIT growth versus 2003.  Mr. Kissner was also responsible for Pitney Bowes’ Corporate Marketing function and launched a corporate-wide Six Sigma program.Mr. Kissner joined Pitney Bowes in January 1995 as President and Chief Executive Officer of Pitney Bowes Credit Corporation.  He is credited with producing strong revenue and profit growth by developing and launching a variety of successful new financial and mailing services products and by maximizing the potential of leasing worldwide.  As Executive Vice President for Small Business and Financial Services (1999-2001), he drove the growth of a new customer base in the small business marketplace and built new direct marketing capabilities in telemarketing, direct mail and the Internet.Mr. Kissner has an extensive background in Services Businesses, with significant line management experience in marketing and strategy, operations, and multi-channel distribution:•        In the area of marketing and strategy, Mr. Kissner’s experience includes consumer, small business and large enterprise/government markets.  During his tenure at Pitney Bowes, Mr. Kissner managed business units serving Enterprise Customers and Small Businesses, as well as Corporate Marketing.  Key accomplishments include introducing successful growth strategies for Enterprise Customers, turning around a failed Small Business Division through application of sophisticated direct marketing techniques, and introducing a new branding strategy for Pitney Bowes.  Mr. Kissner’s consumer marketing experience derives from work at Banker’s Trust, Morgan Stanley and Citibank in particular, where his responsibilities included inbound and outbound telemarketing operations and Director of Marketing for the New York Bank.•        Mr. Kissner has extensive operations experience, including responsibility for a 15,000 person global outsourcing business, sales, service and collections call centers, consumer and business credit, and retail banking branch systems.  In his twenty-six year career, he has successfully led operations through rapid growth as well as consolidations, utilizing a strong process management and six sigma orientation.  Early in his career as a branch manager for Citibank, Mr. Kissner learned the value of direct customer contact.  He has carried this lesson throughout his career, frequently spending time with front line staff and personally calling on customers.•        Mr. Kissner has managed almost every form of distribution, including direct sales forces, call centers, the internet and retail.  He has addressed distribution challenges including multi-level calling and solution selling at enterprise customers, channel conflict between direct sales and other channels, sales force compensation, and CRM across multiple contact points.  His experience in financial services demonstrated the power of technology to enhance the customer experience, build loyalty, improve quality, and reduce cost when well integrated into delivery channels.Mr. Kissner is a board member of John Wiley & Sons, Inc., National Bankruptcy Services Corporation and The Regional Plan Association.  He is a graduate of New York University where he earned his Bachelor of Science and MBA degrees with honors. 
