Executive Profile
Matthew S. Kissner  Chairman of the Board, Interim CEO & Interim President, John Wiley & Sons, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships63$408,750
Background

		Mr. Matthew S. Kissner, also known as Matt, serves as an Operating Partner of Centre Partners Management LLC. Mr. Kissner serves as the President and Chief Executive Officer of The Kissner Group. He has been the Interim Chief Executive Officer at John Wiley & Sons, Inc. since May 8, 2017. Mr. Kissner  serves as Interim President at John Wiley & Sons, Inc. Mr. Kissner is an Operating Partner of Advent International Corporation. He joined Advent International Corporation ... in 2004. At Advent, Mr. Kissner works with the business services and healthcare services buyout teams to identify investment opportunities and advise portfolio companies in both these sectors globally. He has held senior managerial roles at companies such as Pitney Bowes, Bankers Trust Company, Citibank, Morgan Stanley and Westvaco Corporation. He served as President and Chief Executive Officer of EntreCap Financial LLC. Mr. Kissner served as a Consultant of Pitney Bowes Inc., since December 31, 2004. He served as the President, Chief Executive Officer of Pitney Bowes Credit Corp. Mr. Kissner served as an Executive Vice President of Pitney Bowes Inc. and as its Group President of Information Based Solutions and Document Messaging Technologies, from 2001 to December 31, 2004. Prior to that, he was the President of Small Business Solutions at Pitney Bowes Financial Services from 1999 to 2001; President of Pitney Bowes Financial Services from 1997 to 1999 and the President of Pitney Bowes Credit Corporation from 1995 to 1997. He was a Group President of Global Enterprise Solutions. Mr. Kissner has managed multi-channel distribution, geographically dispersed operations and technology-based scalable operations. Mr. Kissner has a track record of achieving double digit revenue and profit growth through developing new business models, creating a strong customer focus and building talent. From January 2006 to December 2007, he was Chairman of American Radiology Services. Mr. Kissner has been Chairman of the Board at John Wiley & Sons, Inc. since October, 2015 and its Director since 2003. He serves as Independent Member at U.S. Retirement Partners, Inc. He serves as Treasurer at Regional Plan Association. He serves as a Director of National Bankruptcy Services and Regional Plan Association. He served as a Director of EntreCap Financial LLC. He served as a Director of Pitney Bowes Credit Corp. He has experience in back office support services and outsourcing across numerous industries which is critical in helping companies develop the operational foundation required for aggressive growth. Mr. Kissner holds an M.B.A. and a B.S., cum laude, from New York University.Read Full Background




